, and checking the bindings could be helpful too. I want to make sure I'm looking at the right resources so that I can understand how everything connects and functions. It's important to gather accurate information to support the user effectively. I'll get started on this exploration now!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MYbTryyeUiosJeVNpb7Qwiwl|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb98c81919e1389a91a09f9c5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw agent --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Mv4QSdEaFHi4aLKT0ZPDRe5t|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb9988191bdc6fa9005b0053a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agents bindings --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw agents bindings --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_WGPlDpYReLK23rT3YZBKlwnA|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb9a08191993f1515a0d270fe","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw channels status --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw channels status --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Fk4c4W30iacyIFxiAH1qE29J|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb9a88191914011691cb10b2b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config --help","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw config --help\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":10003,"output":211,"cacheRead":23424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33638,"cost":{"input":0.025007500000000002,"output":0.0031650000000000003,"cacheRead":0.005856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0340285}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775231638113,"responseId":"resp_065e86cabba226400169cfe298338c8191b3efe395606f9ced"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca260cbc","parentId":"252c45ac","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:54:07.582Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MYbTryyeUiosJeVNpb7Qwiwl|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb98c81919e1389a91a09f9c5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — Less clicking, more shipping, fewer \"where did that file go\" moments.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4142,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — Less clicking, more shipping, fewer \"where did that file go\" moments.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775231647570}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ead81c2","parentId":"ca260cbc","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:54:07.592Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Mv4QSdEaFHi4aLKT0ZPDRe5t|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb9988191bdc6fa9005b0053a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — I don't have opinions about tabs vs spaces. I have opinions about everything else.\n\nUsage: openclaw agents bindings [options]\n\nList routing bindings\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>  Filter by agent id\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n  --json        Output JSON instead of text (default: false)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4154,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — I don't have opinions about tabs vs spaces. I have opinions about everything else.\n\nUsage: openclaw agents bindings [options]\n\nList routing bindings\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>  Filter by agent id\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n  --json        Output JSON instead of text (default: false)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775231647583}}
{"type":"message","id":"4dcfe25d","parentId":"9ead81c2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:54:07.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_WGPlDpYReLK23rT3YZBKlwnA|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb9a08191993f1515a0d270fe","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — Your personal assistant, minus the passive-aggressive calendar reminders.\n\nUsage: openclaw channels status [options]\n\nShow gateway channel status (use status --deep for local)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help      Display help for command\n  --json          Output JSON (default: false)\n  --probe         Probe channel credentials (default: false)\n  --timeout <ms>  Timeout in ms (default: \"10000\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2088,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — Your personal assistant, minus the passive-aggressive calendar reminders.\n\nUsage: openclaw channels status [options]\n\nShow gateway channel status (use status --deep for local)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help      Display help for command\n  --json          Output JSON (default: false)\n  --probe         Probe channel credentials (default: false)\n  --timeout <ms>  Timeout in ms (default: \"10000\")","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775231647592}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c58536e","parentId":"4dcfe25d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:54:07.611Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Fk4c4W30iacyIFxiAH1qE29J|fc_065e86cabba226400169cfe29cb9a88191914011691cb10b2b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — Type the command with confidence—nature will provide the stack trace if needed.\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file/schema/validate). Run without\nsubcommand for guided setup.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configuration sections for guided setup (repeatable). Use\n                       with no subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  schema               Print the JSON schema for openclaw.json\n  set                  Set config values by path (value mode, ref/provider\n                       builder mode, or batch JSON mode).\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\n                       openclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider\n                       default --ref-source env --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\n                       openclaw config set secrets.providers.vault\n                       --provider-source file --provider-path\n                       /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\n                       openclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json\n                       --dry-run\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2015,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.1 (da64a97) — Type the command with confidence—nature will provide the stack trace if needed.\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/unset/file/schema/validate). Run without\nsubcommand for guided setup.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configuration sections for guided setup (repeatable). Use\n                       with no subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  schema               Print the JSON schema for openclaw.json\n  set                  Set config values by path (value mode, ref/provider\n                       builder mode, or batch JSON mode).\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\n                       openclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider\n                       default --ref-source env --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\n                       openclaw config set secrets.providers.vault\n                       --provider-source file --provider-path\n                       /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\n                       openclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json\n                       --dry-run\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775231647600}}
